<section xmlns:ns0="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <num>42-515</num>
  <heading>Expectant estates — Descendible, devisable, and alienable.</heading>
  <text>Expectant estates shall be descendible, devisable, and alienable in the same manner as estates in possession.</text>
  <annotations>
    <annoGroup>
      <heading>History</heading>
      <annotation>Mar. 3, 1901, 31 Stat. 1352, ch. 854, § 1030</annotation>
    </annoGroup>
    <annoGroup>
      <heading>Prior Codifications</heading>
      <annotation>1981 Ed., § 45-215.</annotation>
      <annotation>1973 Ed., § 45-815.</annotation>
    </annoGroup>
  </annotations>
</section>
